The headquarters of the Central  bank of Nigeria was earlier engulfed in thick smoke but CBN authourities said the incident was at the generator house and not the main building. <img class="alignleft wp-image-62049" src="http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/cbn-fire-720x374.jpg" alt="" width="366" height="190" srcset="http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/cbn-fire-720x374.jpg 720w, http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/cbn-fire-150x78.jpg 150w, http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/cbn-fire-420x218.jpg 420w, http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/cbn-fire-768x399.jpg 768w, http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/cbn-fire.jpg 928w" sizes="(max-width: 366px) 100vw, 366px" /> Bello Attahiru, acting assistant commander of the FCT Fire Service who spoke to our correspondent, Akeem Dairo said that the cause of the fire was a mechanical fault from generator number three.    His position was also affirmed by the acting director, corporate communications of the bank, ISAAC Okoroafor who stated that no  part of the main complex was touched and as such no cause for alarm.  Innocent Korie is an ICT and Project Management Professional with very good flair in business development, and social media management. He has a degree in Electronic & Computer Engineering. He is currently stationed at the Online Unit of Nigerian Television Authority